<elements>
  <element name="Nephalem" type="Race" source="5E guide to sex" id="ID__5EGTS_RACE_NEPHALEM">
    <description>
    	<p class="flavor">A Nephalem is an angelic-demonic hybrid, born from the union of a celestial and a fiend. The offspring have a mixture of a celestial and fiend's power and a human soul.</p>
 		<h4>Physical Description</h4>
		<p>Nephalem appear as mostly their humanoid parent race; very few have any features that tell them apart from their fellow man if they don't use their devil forms; an ability known as Devil Trigger to them. Being similar in build and age for the first couple of decades, making them appear nearly undying beings as they do tend to recover from impalings with great finesse.</p>
 		<h4>Untapped Potential</h4>
		<p>Due to their lineage the extent of their power is often varied, as some only manifest a friction of their lineage power while others might even surpass the power of gods.</p>
      	<h4>History</h4>
		<p>Nephalem is a term for a hybrid conceived from a celestial and a fiend creature.Due to t</p>
      	<p class="indent"> </p>
		<h4>Society</h4> 
      	<p>As they aren't usually different from humans: Nephalem take to social places like any other human race, rarely being picked out by any non-demon or -devil blooded creatures. Though most hunt devils and demons alike, few find a quiet life more accomplishing than a loud bloody one.</p>
      	<h4>Nephalem Traits</h4>
      	<p class="indent"><strong><em>Ability Score Increase.</em></strong> Your Dexterity increased by 1 and Constitution by 2.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Age.</em></strong> Nephalem reach maturity at the same age as humans, attaining immortality at the peak of their maturity.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Alignment.</em></strong> Due to their unnatural origin there is no set alignment.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Size.</em></strong> Nephalem are the same size as humans. Your size is Medium.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Speed.</em></strong> Your base walking speed is 30 feet.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Truesight.</em></strong> You can see in normal and magical darkness, see invisible creatures and objects, automatically detect visual illusions and succeed on saving throws against them, perceive the original form of a shapechanger or a creature that is transformed by magic, and see into the Ethereal Plane, all within a range of 120 feet.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Keen Senses.</em></strong> You have proficiency in the Perception skill.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Celestial Resistance.</em></strong> You have resistance to necrotic damage and radiant damage.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Hellish Resistance.</em></strong> You have resistance to fire damage.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Infernal Legacy.</em></strong> You know the thaumaturgy cantrip. Once you reach 3rd level, you can cast the hellish rebuke spell once per day as a 2nd-level spell. Once you reach 5th level, you can also cast the darkness spell once per day. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for these spells.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Devil Trigger.</em></strong> You have resistance to fire damage.</p>
		<p class="indent"><strong><em>Languages.</em></strong> You can speak, read, and write Common, Abyssal, Draconic, Celestial, and Infernal.</p>
    </description>
    <rules>
